%^RESET%^%^BOLD%^%^GREEN%^Prestige Class
%^RESET%^%^CYAN%^Eldritch Knight:

%^RESET%^%^CYAN%^Requirements:
%^RESET%^%^CYAN%^ %^RESET%^ Level 20 Base class
%^RESET%^%^CYAN%^ %^RESET%^ Martial Weapon Proficiency
%^RESET%^%^CYAN%^ %^RESET%^ Spell focus
%^RESET%^%^CYAN%^ %^RESET%^ Non-Psionic Base Class

%^RESET%^%^CYAN%^Hitdice:%^RESET%^ same as base class
%^RESET%^%^CYAN%^Class Feats:%^RESET%^
 %^RESET%^L1: eldritch conditioning
 %^RESET%^L4: eldritch warfare
 %^RESET%^L7: spell critical

Fearsome warriors and spellcasters, eldritch knights are rare among magic-users in their ability to wade into battle alongside fighters, barbarians, and other martial classes. Those who must face an eldritch knights in combat fear them greatly, for their versatility on the battlefield is tremendous. Against heavily armed and armored opponents they may level crippling spells, while opposing spellcasters meet their ends on an eldritch knight's blade.

%^RESET%^%^CYAN%^See also: %^RESET%^feats, skills, spells, cast, kill
